Subject: [PATCH] of: unittest: Disable interrupt node tests for old world MAC
 systems
References: bnc#1012628
Patch-mainline: 4.18.14
Git-commit: 8894891446c9380709451b99ab45c5c53adfd2fc

commit 8894891446c9380709451b99ab45c5c53adfd2fc upstream.

On systems with OF_IMAP_OLDWORLD_MAC set in of_irq_workarounds, the
devicetree interrupt parsing code is different, causing unit tests of
devicetree interrupt nodes to fail. Due to a bug in unittest code, which
tries to dereference an uninitialized pointer, this results in a crash.

